place_description: Beer , wine, espresso, snacks, toys and fun!! A gathering place for everyone.

reviews_data.review_text: Terrible. My fiance ordered a HOLY CHEESES and it came out burnt. Are you kidding me? How do you mess up a grilled cheese sandwich? The whole ordering process was a nightmare. I didn't appreciate paying beforehand either. And the screen asked if I wanted to tip 18%, 20%, 25%? For what? You do everything yourself here. You get your own drinks and refills. Here's a buzzer, come get your food. This place sucks. It's just a convenience store without a fryer because you can't get fries with your burger, so I hope you like chips. How this place calls itself a restaurant is beyond me. I guess gas stations, Walmart, and anywhere else you can get a drink and a sandwich is a restaurant now too.
Great service, food and atmosphere. I'm vegan and they have several choices for me which I really appreciate!

They play music with crazy levels of profanity and sexual themes. Not the best experience while trying to eat a meal. Straight up disgusting if you listen to the lyrics. Songs played at around 6pm 2.4.25 Switched to country after patrons complained. Food was average. Environment was interesting.

The place is not huge inside, but there is plenty of of room outside. The food is great, the Bahn You and the Pimpy Longstocking are amazing.  Great selection of beers and they also have some cool knick knacks. If you're in Monroe, don't skip this place.
Love everything on the menu!

What an experience! I got the Harry S Truben & Steak Fries with a Pink Lemonade.
The atmosphere is very unique and if I'm back in the area I'll try something new on the menu. Food was great and not expensive.
This place is a breath of fresh air! Awesome food, service and beer/wine selection.

This place has good vibes and friendly service. Me and my friends popped in on a Saturday and it was super chill. Got the steak sandwich and it was good af. Also the apple cranberry cobbler was good maybe a 7.5/10. We also got some beer & wine. It was a great place to spend time with friends.
My favorite place to eat in Monroe! Great every time. Eclectic atmosphere

Absolute best place to eat in Monroe! Any of the one star reviews are from people that probably didn't go there and just trying to be hateful. Highly recommend the Monday special which is the Downtown Scandal sandwich and their bagel sandwiches! Also love the Philly cheese steak. The owners are wonderful and always super friendly
Great place where everyone is seen and welcome!
An awesome find. Definitely coming back here again.
Love this uniquely esthetic Superette. Food is fantastic, an eclectic menu that tempts your palate. The choices for beverages and sides are amazing! Love this place.
Great place
Great food, drink and atmosphere.

Sept 2022: Such a cool place! We didn't find it until the end of June but we've been SO many times since. Sunday brunch was yummy. Monday's Scandal was scandalously good. Taco Tuesday's street tacos were terrific. Wednesday's Big Ass Burritos were DEFINITELY big ass burritos.  Thursday's free "wine" tasting was informative. (We tasted sake, which we'd never had before.) Friday's Brisket was to die for. Saturday's, I'm in and out for drinks and food while playing PokemonGo! The atmosphere, camaraderie, and overall sense of being "at home" in this place will bring you back again and again! (It obviously did ME anyway!)
July 2022: we are still regulars at East Frank because it's not just a food place. It's also the hangout for old, and new, friends, and chosen family. I would never have thought that people eating at a restaurant or going out for drinks would become family, but they did.
This place also has Trivia and Drag nights that are great fun for all!
Nov 2024: We still love EF for their food and fun atmosphere. They have a lot of the same familiar menu but add new delicious items in constantly.
Cool little spot for good eats!

Everyone at East Frank is always kind and accepting of others! The food is super yummy and there's lots of options for vegetarians and vegans!! overall great vibes I always take friends and family to visit!! y'all are amazing! :)

East Frank is by far my favorite restaurant in all of Union county. Everything I have tried from them has been fantastic. The staff are absolutely wonderful, they are the true heart of this establishment. They are the reason I visit East Frank every week, sometimes multiple visits a week. xoxo

My boo and I are at East Frank almost every Sunday for brunch. We are also there some week nights for dinner.

The vibe is immaculate. The staff is kind. The selection of craft beer is out of this world. And please do not even get me started on the food!! (But if you were to get me started on the food, I'd rave about the breakfast bahn mi. And their hot chicken!!)
East Frank is a fun place to go to. The food is always delicious too.
I love this place! Great food, amazing alcohol selection, and friendly staff! Only reason I gave 4 stars for food is because they are small portions for a high price but everything tastes great
Very, very good food and service!!! Will come again.
If I could give higher than 5 stars I would. Food was amazing and so was the atmosphere. I will definitely be back.
Love going here! Great place to take my friends when they come to town!

I am a regular here up
Until the last 2 weeks last week I came in had a beer and chips and was told my 13 month old was causing issues when he was just fussy had he been screaming I would had left now one week later we are there for a while with no issues as soon as my son made a peep the owner came up to us and said he was causing a problem.. of course they waited till I paid and tipped I've worked in the industry for 17 years and not a single owner would consider this for a place that says they don't discriminate they do against kids I called after and was told it's a "bad look to have a baby at a bar" when it's not it's a convenient store with take out I've never been more insulted I moved here from mass to get away from places like this and they deff are not who they say they are I mean it was 4:00 on a Tuesday why can't my child be there?
One of the most unique and inclusive places in downtown Monroe! Excellent food and drink options! Vegetarian options. Retro novelties to purchase. Fabulous entertainment offerings!
Didn't eat today.

This is such a fun place!  The atmosphere is colorful and eclectic (even in the restrooms). There are so many yummy items on the menu.  I had the Thai peanut wrap with tofu and a side of grits. It was so good. There is a lot to look at while you are trying to decide on your order, and the staff at the counter were patient and helpful. There is a selection of interesting packaged beverages, candies, and chips available for purchase, and a quirky selection of novelty toys for sale. We had a lot of laughs looking at these while we waited for our order.  Also fun - their fountain soda dispenser has Cheerwine. I appreciate the thoughtful vegetarian options as well.
Awesome place!

The BANH YOU is to diiieeee fooorrrr!! We've been here a few times and love the atmosphere of it, the quirky gifts, the huge chocolate bars, and most of all the food and service! This place is highly recommend
Amazing food, I can wait to go again.
Love the food and the environment at East Frank! Already excited to go back and try something new from the menu.
I can't get enough of this whole establishment! Love it!
The sandwiches are the best in the Charlotte area. Always love chatting with the staff, and looking around at the kitschy things on the wall.

Eclectic restaurant with good quality food at reasonable prices. I recommend the pastrami brisket sandwich. They have a great rotation of daily specials. There is always something new to discover on their menu.
Friendly staff and that's how you do a chili cheese dog best one I've had in a while thanks

The grill across the street is 1000 times better. Here though, I'm sure I won't be able to eat salt for a month, I cant wash this taste out of my mouth, and the food was colder than a dairy queen blizzard.
Reminded us of college bar

The cutest little surprise in downtown Monroe. I needed a place to grab lunch since I was going to be on the road all day. I found this on Google and they had amazing reviews. The space did not disappoint.
I loved the homey and electric feel of the place. It has a coffee shop, gift shop, wine/beer shop, and kitchen. It literally had it all!
I enjoyed the Banh You with a gluten free wrap and it was so good!
Amazing options no matter what your dietary restrictions are!!
I will definitely make special trips out to Monroe just to go here.
Love this place! It's a funky whole in the wall with the most amazing vibe and food!!! Their take on the Reuben is delicious!
Love East Frank, great food, awesome veggie burger and steak fries.  Great and fun atmosphere.
I enjoy their tasty sandwiches in the easy-going environment. You can even get hot sauce, beer or whole bean coffee to-go as part of their grocery store.

Great place to grab a drink, lots of great beer, seltzer and other Choices  . Funky vibes and locals having food that looked really good . We didn't eat but the food service window was super busy on a Saturday afternoon.
Very friendly. Great food. Great atmosphere. Sandwiches are exceptional!
Always a good time! Great food and drinks, friendly staff, amazing vibe, fun entertainment!
4/20/24 Drag Bingo...fun as always.
I love this place so much. This is my favorite spot in Monroe to eat or just hang out. The food is fantastic and so are the people.
Always interesting and good food

Went there on a whim for breakfast then afterwards decided to go back for lunch! Total vibe and they have a vast drinking selection from local beers to ciders and wines to match. Definitely going to recommend to friends/family and make this a normal hangout spot
Had the "Hummus Amongus" listening to blue grass. As a queer hillbilly from the mountains of Virginia, I could not have asked for more! The music was great and the food delicious!

I'm sure they have the adult beverage your looking for and the hotdogs are great. Eclectic type of vibe in Monroe. Great lil hang out on the sidewalk and watch the happenings of town place. Service was great. The cashier/order taker dude was very engaging and offered assistance several times while I perused the menu board.
Quirky place with excellent food. Takes food allergies seriously.

Great place that a friend recommended us to go to on our way out of town.  Food was amazing and all the things in the shop were great to look at while waiting for food! Stop by for sure bc if not missing out.
Not possible to say enough good things about thus place. Great food and staff. Cool vibes. Stop in for sure!
My favorite spot to stop in for a cappuccino and friendly faces! Don't miss it, East Frank adds a whole dimension to downtown Monroe.

My friend suggested that I go there with my daughter for lunch!  This place is amazing!  Love the vibe and energy!  The staff is very friendly and helpful!  We ordered the Thai chicken wrap.   We omitted a few ingredients and asked for the sauces on the side.   The wrap was delicious!  We will definitely make the 1hr 45 minutes road trip to eat here again.
Everything about it was great, food was top notch, very cool fun vibe to the whole place, and everyone we talked with were super friendly, it felt like visiting an old friends house!
Very unique place
First timer and can I say I will always be back when in town!!

didn't try the food. you can have beer, play pinball, and they sell some cool stuff like various hot sauces, candies, and more.
Staff is super nice too.

The place is not very clean, tables were dirty and bathrooms have not been cleaned. Food was ok I had better. They had a drag queen show promoting cross dressing to little kids. Not taking my business here again and would recommend going somewhere else would not expect something like this from a place that should only worry about providing food not an LGBTQ agenda.
Everyone is welcome at East Frank Superette. Fun eclectic atmosphere with many snack and sandwich choices along with your favorite adult or non-alcohol beverage.

This place is awesome!!! The vibe in there is incredible, it's super cozy and there's a lot to look at in there so you won't get bored. They had pride flags out front which made me feel super comfortable and welcome. This is a really good spot for a casual date or hangout, especially with how much stuff is within walking distance.
Great place to visit.
Fantastic food and service! Great selection, fun atmosphere! Everyone welcomed!
Great Place, Great Food and Wonderful People and Staff.. .

UPDATE: I want it clear, I still love East Frank. The vibe and the people are right. The food, however, has definitely fallen off as of late. The brunswick stew was once the best I had ever tried. After ordering it today, I'm not sure I'll ever order it again. Not good. I asked a couple other friends if I was alone in this feeling, and unfortunately, it's the same for others. I will update again if/when they get the food back right!!

Great craft selection. Lovely little menu.
I had the Athena salad with grilled chicken and it was delicious. My husband got the gluten-free bread. Reuben. It's a fun and great place to get good food and relax with one you love.
An adorable little enclave in stodgy downtown Monroe.  Good food, fun place.  Very unique.  The furthest thing from a franchise you ever see. Gluten friendly options are available.
Tasty cheesesteak. Can get pricey if you buy extras with your meal
Really awesome place. I had one of the best burgers Ive ever eaten here. Definitely will visit again. And got some toys for the kiddo.

This was such a pleasant surprise!  The sandwich selection was amazing.  Most items can be made gluten free with GF bread or wrap.  My cheese steak sandwich on GF bread was phenomenal.  Husband really liked his Reuben.  Garlic cheese grits were so good.  Retro vibes all around (RIP Pee Wee) including a well-curated selection of 80s toys and candy.   Staff was friendly and very helpful with the GF stuff.  Will definitely make it a point to stop here again when traveling through Monroe.  11 out of 10 stars

I was visiting with my boyfriend from out of town and we absolutely love this spot! I wish we would have found this on the first day. Amber made our visit so pleasant and warm. She had excellent recommendations and overall has a killer instinct with service. I couldn't recommend more! Get beer to go too!

Funky place with an
Asheville vibe. Great sandwich and positive folks.
Absolutely love this place! The food is SO GOOD and they have vegan/gluten free options. The gifts and decor are quirky fun! We visit as often as possible

The menu at East Frank Superette and Kitchen offers a delightful fusion of flavors. The variety of options available catered to a range of dietary preferences, ensuring there is something for everyone.

The service at East Frank Superette and Kitchen is always top-notch. The staff is always attentive, knowledgeable, and friendly. They are more than happy to answer any questions  that you have  and provide excellent recommendations.

I highly recommend East Frank Superette and Kitchen. My favorite place to go when visiting downtown Monroe!

Amber suggested that I didn't pay for my meal, after being told by the cashier that I actually did pay. She was very rude and it was embarrassing because other's customers started to look at me as if I was trying to steal food. I order with server Robot Boy C and was asked kindly to pay at next register, which I did and then I went back to pick up my order, but Amber took my order to the register where I had already paid. I called when I arrived home to speak with a manager and Amber answered and again was rude and took no accountability for her rudeness. I will never visit this establishment again! This has absolutely nothing to do with the owner's, I was intrigued to them by the hair salon next door.
Love this local spot! 10/10s all around.
This place is amazing! Burgers and rueban are sooooo good!!

I've been here a couple of times. The food is nothing to write home about. There are some cool old school products you can buy but now that I know they have drag queen shows for minors, I won't be back. I had no clue this was going on in my town. DISGUSTING!

Un lugar muy bonito, tiene muchos detalles, comida, dulces, snacks y bebidas muy variadas. Muy rica la comida y a buen precio, hay varios articulos que tiene a la venta. Lugar curioso y muy interesante

I have been so many times but recently I tried the vegan Evil Cheesesteak & the Go Big or Go Homer and...oh my gosh. It was everything I could hope for and more. I'm so grateful we have somewhere in Monroe with SO many vegan options!
Thank you, Thank you, Thank you. THANK YOU. Great food. Excellent merch. But honestly? Beautiful community. More. More. MORE.

Great place to go hang out and grab some good food. They have regular trivia nights and all sorts of other fun events. Great selection of beer on tap and in the vast rows of refrigerators. They also have a few pinball and arcade machines. Great place. Don't miss it.

All around great place.  Owners were active. Open early. Had the veggie burrito every and I want another...   so many thing in the space. Now games, snacks, wine exc... I couldn't focus 
It was a fun experience. Even Got me a yoyo and some taffy..
So much fun! Great crowd, so welcoming!

Nice spot in downtown Monroe. People were all great. Has a nice low-key atmosphere. Excellent lunch spot with ample seating. I ordered a banh-mi sandwich and a side of potato salad. It definitely didn't leave me disappointed but seemed fairly par. The combination of the space, availability of food, and decent tap list along with a fair selection  of packaged goods make it a really great spot where each of those things on their own would be fairly ordinary.

Bottom line, if I lived in the area, I'd definitely go back again. I'd be willing to bet they have something on their food menu that is killer.

There's a good chance I'll go again this weekend and most times when I visit.
Good vegan options! I love the colorful, playful decor.
We LOVE our monthly meet-up and enjoy the show and food!! So happy we hVe a place like East Franks!

Great place. Kind fun people.  Huge selection of beers, ciders, and non alcoholic drinks - lots of local options. Vegan options and options for the carnivores.  They were kind about the customization requirements of our families dietary needs. :-)

This is becoming my favorite place to go for lunch or a nice meal out with my hubby and plan to bring my daughters, son and granddaughter at some point too!

The staff is friendly and the atmosphere feels fantastic!!! We didn't have tickets for the Drag show this time but as of today, it is on my MUST ATTEND list for future date nights!

The food is fun and I enjoy the variations they come up with to bring new life to the same old dish everyone attempts to serve. The wine and beer selections are awesome and a wonderful eclectic array to choose from.

Fun place. Great food. Amazing selection of things to drink 
Always really good
Food is delicious and service was great. Love the welcoming atmosphere. Don't listen to any of the haters.
Their menu is interesting but also most everything I've gotten has been good! Their chilimac is my favorite. Their entertainment throughout the week is also top-notch.

Food was really good, we loved the atmosphere, the service was okay. Seemed as if the staff didn't care to serve anyone they didn't already know, no one was rude, just not as friendly as the environment.
Always enjoy a visit here.  Good sandwiches and great selection of ciders for sale.
Fantastic  my birthday was Tuesday July 4th the only place open to eat in downtown Monroe. Also got my beer for a dollar.. Tuesday is $2 off draft beers.
Dope spot w/ dope people & delicious food!

I went to East Frank's for a quick bite on a Sunday morning. I had my 2 frenchies with me so I sat outside and had to call in my order. They were happy to bring my order outside and take my payment (only service dogs are allowed inside).

I ordered the Pimpin' Grits and they were wonderful. The grits were cooked perfectly and topped with eggs and pimiento cheese- I added sausage as my protein. I'll absolutely be back while I'm in town...I've got my eye on the meatloaf sandwich :)

This place is bursting with charm and a wonderful selection of delicious food and beverages, not to mention a fantastic eccentric atmosphere that welcomes people of all ages, races, and orientations. If you're from Charlotte you will adore how similar East Frank Superette and Kitchen is to The Common Market, a CLT landmark. The location of EFS&K is very convenient and the intersection where it's located boasts an adorable small-town Main Street feel, loaded with shopping and dining choices, along with beautiful landscaping/upkeep. We love East Frank!
Very fun, eclectic place with a great menu. Plenty of vegetarian options. Big variety of beer and wine for sale.
This place is quirky and fantastic. Love Funroe!!
A wonderful place that treats you like family, couldnt recommend more!

I had hot chocolate here with oat milk and raspberry flavoring. It was a warm comfort drink.

The variety of sandwiches on offer is astounding. I ended up ordering the breakfast banh mi and it was big enough for two people. I came hungry and left with a full belly.

I'm mad at how good the Peruvian dog is. Just stop EF, plz. So good!! I've had nearly all the specials and most of the menu and there is something for EVERY TYPE OF PERSON AND TASTE!! Most everything is made in house. The collaborations with local businesses, contributions to the community and a location where you can be yourself while having a pint, coffee or maybe some food while looking around at the eclectic assortment of knickknacks  makes this spot one of a kind!!
Wonderful food, drinks, and people. We really needed a place like this in Monroe. It's my favorite local hangout!
i absolutely love this place so much! such a safe and fun environment!!
A very fun and cool spot! We all enjoyed breakfast,  and I had an awesome breakfast salad.
This is such a fun place the food Is delicious the staff is great kids are welcome 10/10  recommend

I had a vegetarian breakfast wrap that they customized for me along with the sweet potato hash. It was great! The food was delicious, customer service was very pleasant, and the vibes were welcoming. I would definitely return when I'm in town again.
Fun place, good food, friendly staff and patrons. Great addition to the growing downtown Monroe food and drink scene.

Absolute best cheesesteak and mac and cheese I've ever had. Wouldn't have known about this place if it wasn't for the lovely people outside with their signs and kind words promoting the drag show a few Saturdays ago. Love the free publicity! I'll definitely be coming back to try more of the menu :)
Great food, amazing and unique decor, fantastic entertainment, super friendly staff, and an inclusive, welcoming vibe. I tell people about this place all the time!
such a wonderful and accepting place. their food is incredible and they have a MASSIVE drink selection (alcoholic and not!). highly, highly recommended!!
Comfortable atmosphere and great service.

Every time I come into this restaurant I always have an interesting experience. I love the decor and this dude on the napkin box!! The food is delicious and today's turkey sandwich was it was just banging good! I highly recommend coming to visit at East Frank Superette and Kitchen. They have some great events to check out as well that are very inclusive  to all!!
Nice little chill hang out spot, or jus get some food
What an amazing night! Great food, great people, great place! I will most definitely be back! I have never been to drag queen bingo and I had such a great time! Thank you all for being so wonderful!
Really good food and a great atmosphere! Lots of vegetarian and vegan options!
It was so good I was back for breakfast the next day unusual and delicious menu every single bite will melt your brain

This place is too good.  The food is off the charts- it's really culinary greatness.  Beer and wine selection on point, awesome specials, all kinds of cool events from poetry readings, music, trivia, etc.  I like their all-seeing eye "sees all serves all" motto-  you can tell they take customer service seriously and truly care for their customers and the community.
It's overpriced bland food.
Great food, coffee, and mimosas. The staff is spectacular.

I tell everyone about East Frank! If you're from New York or New Jersey, I highly recommend the Jersey Shore breakfast sandwich here. It's the only thing I'm a morning person for lol. Not to mention the decor is so fun and kitschy!
Love that this place has vegan options,  a friendly staff and cool atmosphere  :)
My new favorite spot! Great food, drinks,  staff and atmosphere.
I love this place

All I can say is wow !!! This place is fire ! I just got Uber eats about 20 minutes ago and had to hop on here to leave a review!!! I got the Evil Cheesesteak sandwich and a side of Mac. Mac was 8.5/10. Philly was 10/10. Amazing. I will definitely be back !!!

Brunch was so yummy!  There was something for everyone too!  We had multiple things from the menu and couldn't stop eating all of them!  Great, chill atmosphere paired with amazing food and a solid drink selection. We will be back soon!  Thank for having such a cool spot!!!
Great place to meet friends for a drink.
Cool atmosphere and great food.
Eclectic and inviting. So happy I don't have to drive to CLT to have a little slice of CM here in Monroe.
Awesome little place .  There is plenty to see while waiting on food to be made.  Went there with a few people from work and we were all satisfied with the food.

Went for dinner spent 55 on food for two and drinks for all night (which was amazing and delicious,) stayed for the drag show and bingo. Protesters did show but East Frank employees handled everything with grace and professionalism. The show was absolutely amazing and everyone was so beautiful. Will definitely be going back and recommend you go at least once!
Food is incredible every time we've been.  Love the atmosphere, very laid back.
Great food & service!
Great food, great service, great atmosphere.  Really good decorations and items for sale.
Great sandwiches and a wide variety of beverages and gifts...Can't wait to go back. Very friendly waitstaff.
Awesome employees!  great food I will definitely be going back
Great service, atmosphere, cold beers and food. 100% recommend this place.
Favorite business, hands down in Monroe! Their food, beer, and wine selection covers all the wants! Eclectic, fun, with stellar people working there with great events and entertainment!

Love stopping at East Frank when I'm in town! Great inclusive vibe, outdoor patio, and lots of great beer options to enjoy inside or take home. The food I've had has been great as well. Stop by for food/drink, grab something to take home, buy a gift, hear some music, play some bingo...what a great spot for the area!
Amazing staff, and an amazing environment! Seems like the workers all love being there, which is more than you can say for fast food
Brilliant community of folks sharing the love. Healing and joyful place of inclusion and deliciousness!  Great vegan options!
My daughter and I love this place! Great food, wine and people.
Had a Thai wrap with tofu. Food is consistently good. Love the atmosphere. Friendly staff. Great music too!!!!
Big Ole Breakfast Burrito & Snickerdoodle coffee was all I needed to take on the morning! Great pricing and great menu options.
This place is the best. No other place like it.
Great place with absolutely the coolest atmosphere and the best food. Incredible beer and wine selection and the owners are awesome.
Very expensive for what they offer. Atmosphere more like a bar, and service is counter only. I'd rank the food a 5.
I absolutely love this place!! It has all the vibes! Stranger Things trivia night was a blast for the whole family. This is a great addition to the already amazing downtown Monroe scene.
This is a great addition to dow town Monroe. We are so lucky to have this establishment. Very grateful for their contributions to the community!!
Great sandwiches great service,  will definitely be back!
We love East Frank!  Coolest digs in town!!!
Incredible atmosphere and service.
A cool funky place with great subs & cold beer and beverages plus a whole lot more
Friendly staff. Great food. Solid beer selection (draft and bottle). Fun date night. My kids enjoy the classic candies and sodas.
Very unique little store/restaurant. Food was grear and portions are good. Would definitely recommend.
Awesome place run by awesome people.  Food was good,  and they live up to the name "Superette"  with a very big variety of items offered.  It will become a regular spot for us.
Funkiest eatery around. Meatloaf sandwich is awesome. Great selection of beer and sodas. They have Big Red soda in bottles (real sugar).  You must go here for the eats and the experience.
This place rules
Food was very good. I love the vibe. This place is a great addition to Monroe. This town needs more of this eclectic approach.

A very nice little spot for good food and a great atmosphere. The people working are all nice. Will definitely keep patronizing this establishment. Also a very good place to go if you have a vegan/vegetarian diet. They also have a very wide selection of alcohol and sodas to choose from.
Great food and an even better staff even though Becca turned off a song I was enjoying. She won't get a Christmas card this year.
Great food. Interesting and different menu. Fun atmosphere with live music.
We always love it here. The food is great and I love the unique specials. The kids love to look in the store.
Great food. Slightly eclectic...Korean hot dog with kimchi. Wonderful. Peruvian chicken sandwich. Delicious. Friendly staff. Fun place to eat. Huge beer selection.

Absolutely love this place!  My wife and I have been coming here for about as long as they've been open.  They have a great selection of drinks and snacks, and the food is AMAZING!  We love them so much, we asked them to cater our wedding!
Summer Drag Brunch! It was a blast! TALT w/bacon was great.

Such a neat restaurant! The food was amazing. I got the cheesesteak and my wife got the reuben. We will absolutely come back, as they were two of the best sandwiches we've had in a long time! The staff was nice and overall the restaurant is chill, albeit interesting. Give it a shot!
Delicious food, and a great all-welcoming vibe.  Funky and fun things to look at while you enjoy your food.  They host all kinds of  great events too.  You won't be disappointed.
They have the BEST Pimento Cheese!!  They are very friendly and helpful!!
Food is delicious and East Frank has the best beer selection in Monroe!  Definitely try the Banh sandwich, it was amazing!
Love how quirky this place is. The shop is great and the food and scenery is cool.

This place is AMAZING. The food is the best in Mornoe with something for everyone (including those with food restrictions like gluten allergies and vegans). All good is delicious, people are lovely, and it's just a fun and inclusive place.
Delicious food, fantastic atmosphere. A nice, colorful oasis in the heart of Monroe
Unique atmosphere with amazing freshly prepared food.

Stumpled in by pure accident on our road trip through the Carolinas in 2019. Boy: What a store. The nicest people, the nicest collection of Star Trek Dishes and the nicest everything. At that point, I believe to remember, the store was pretty new and an addition to the first of its kind near/in (?) Charlotte. I am excited and very glad that it still exists and it seems the whole neighborhood has developed. If you aren't from the area but on your way from A to B: definitely stop by. All the best from Germany.

(P.S.: I lived in Berlin for the past 10 years and never saw a place as cool as East Frank Superette and Kitchen. This either means I have no idea about Berlin ... or as I like to think: EFSK is just awesome.)

Not impressed sadly. We didnt even get to try the food, because as we walked in, my 10 year old was greeted with an inappropriate poster. Never greeted by a human. She didn't feel comfortable there. "Sketchy" in her words. I see a lot of people that love the place, and we really wanted to try it, but it was an uncomfortable scene. We went across the street to The Grille at Franklin Court where it was definitely more family friendly.

Get your sh!t together when it comes to events on your web site and FB page. Times are incorrect, there are no links or indication for what needs tickets or
How to get them. Specific example website says drag bingo 6:30 6/4. No indication tickets are needed or references to go to FB. People are not mind readers. Also FB is not updated to indicate how to get tickets or if something is sold out.  Get both updated to be accurate.
A unique place with great sandwiches!
The food is always amazing and we love the atmosphere.
there pimpin grits are the best grits i have ever had
Great food, fun friends, cold beverages. Who could ask for more.

East Frank is the BOMB!!  Their menu is diverse with lots of vegetarian options, hours are accommodating, staff is friendly, coffee and lattes are superb, and a huge variety of beers and soda in glass bottles!  If you haven't been yet, I urge you to check them out!!

As if that isn't enough, they regularly give back to the community by donating supporting local nonprofits like Council on Aging and the Community Shelter.

My Dad and Grandad ran a hardware store for 60 years in the location now occupied by East Frank. I only went for a purely nostalgic visit to see the old place again.
But I was so pleasantly surprised to find such a cool local business! Friendly staff, an eclectic mix of foods, drinks and candy. They even had my absolute favorite vinho verde wine in the cooler!
Wonderful shop that I hope will carry on the local business legacy of that location for the next 60 years!
